text: Fjälkinge is a town in Kristianstad Municipality, Skåne County, Sweden. 1,690 persons lived there in 2010. The name, Fjälkinge, may mean "steep hill". Fjälkinge Church is a Romanesque-style church with paintings made in the 1200s. Olof Hanson, an American building designer, was born in Fjälkinge in 1862. His family moved to Willmar, Minnesota in 1875. == References == Category:Settlements in Skane County
